def draw_image(img):
    plt.imshow(img,cmap='gray')
    plt.show()
    
p = Path("Desktop/SRIB/img")
images = []
masks = []

cnt = 0
for i in sorted(p.glob("*.jpg")):
    string = str(i)
    img = cv2.imread(string)
    img = cv2.cvtColor(img, cv2.COLOR_BGR2GRAY)
    img = cv2.resize(img,(256,256))
    images.append(img)
    cnt += 1
print(cnt)

cnt1 = 0
for i in sorted(p.glob("*.png")):

    img = cv2.cvtColor(img, cv2.COLOR_BGR2GRAY)
    img = cv2.resize(img,(256,256))
    masks.append(img)
    cnt1 += 1
print(cnt1)

autoencoder = Sequential()
autoencoder.add(Conv2D(32, (5,5), activation='relu', padding='same', input_shape=(256, 256,1)))
autoencoder.add(Conv2D(32, (5,5), activation='relu', padding='same'))
autoencoder.add(Dropout(0.2))
autoencoder.add(Conv2D(1, (5,5), padding='same'))
sgd = optimizers.SGD(lr=0.01)
autoencoder.summary()
autoencoder.compile(optimizer=sgd, loss='binary_crossentropy')
autoencoder.fit(X_, Y_, epochs=25)

test = []
original = []
p1 = Path("Desktop/img")
cnt = 0
for i in (p1.glob("*.jpg")):
    if cnt > 20:
        break
    string = str(i)
    img = cv2.imread(string)
    img = cv2.resize(img,(256,256))
    original.append(img)
    img = cv2.cvtColor(img, cv2.COLOR_BGR2GRAY)
    test.append(img)
    cnt += 1

X_test = np.array(test)/255.0
